---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contribute - Skillsets.cc">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8 border-b border-border-ink pb-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium font-serif text-text-ink">Contribute a Skillset</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="border border-border-ink bg-stone-50 p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink border-b border-border-ink pb-2 inline-block">What We're Looking For</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4 font-serif leading-relaxed">
        Unlike atomic skill marketplaces or limited examples, skillsets.cc indexes
        <strong class="text-text-ink">production-verified workflows</strong> — validated combinations
        of skills, agents, hooks, plugins, and MCP configurations that have shipped real software.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-transparent p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-6 text-text-ink">Submission Process</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            1
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif text-text-ink mb-2">Initialize Your Skillset</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3 font-serif">
              Run the init command in your project directory. It will auto-detect existing
              <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">.claude/</code> and
              <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">CLAUDE.md</code> files.
            </p>
            <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>npx skillsets init</code></pre>
            <p class="text-text-tertiary mt-3 font-serif text-sm">
              Creates: <code class="font-mono">skillset.yaml</code>, <code class="font-mono">README.md</code>,
              <code class="font-mono">PROOF.md</code>, <code class="font-mono">content/</code>, and installs the audit skill
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            2
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif mb-2 text-text-ink">Add Production Proof</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3 font-serif">
              Edit <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">PROOF.md</code>
              with evidence of your skillset in production: project links, metrics, or links to videos/writeups.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            3
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif mb-2 text-text-ink">Run the Structural Audit</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3 font-serif">
              Validate your skillset structure and generate an audit report.
            </p>
            <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>npx skillsets audit</code></pre>
            <p class="text-text-tertiary mt-3 font-serif text-sm">
              Tier 1: manifest schema, required files, content structure, file sizes, secrets detection
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            4
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif mb-2 text-text-ink">Run the Qualitative Review</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3 font-serif">
              Once structural audit passes, run the qualitative review <strong class="text-text-ink">in the repo where you used the skillset</strong>.
            </p>
            <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>/skillset-audit [AUDIT_REPORT.md]</code></pre>
            <p class="text-text-tertiary mt-3 font-serif text-sm">
              Tier 2: evaluates primitives against best practices and verifies workflow artifacts
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            5
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif mb-2 text-text-ink">Submit via CLI</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3 font-serif">
              Once your audit passes, submit directly from the command line.
              Requires <a href="https://cli.github.com/" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub CLI</a> installed and authenticated.
            </p>
            <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>npx skillsets submit</code></pre>
            <p class="text-text-tertiary mt-3 font-serif text-sm">
              This forks the registry, creates a branch, and opens a PR automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-orange-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold font-mono">
            6
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-serif mb-2 text-text-ink">Review & Merge</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary font-serif">
              Maintainers will review your production proof and validate the audit report.
              Once approved, your skillset will be published to the registry.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-border-ink bg-stone-50 p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink border-b border-border-ink pb-2 inline-block">Quick Reference</h2>
      <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code># Initialize (scaffolds structure + installs audit skill)
npx skillsets init

# Tier 1: Structural validation
npx skillsets audit

# Tier 2: Qualitative review (in reference repo)
/skillset-audit [AUDIT_REPORT.md]

# Submit PR to registry (requires gh CLI)
npx skillsets submit</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-transparent p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink">Updating an Existing Skillset</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4 font-serif leading-relaxed">
        Already have a skillset in the registry? The same commands work for updates.
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-text-secondary font-serif">
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Bump the version</strong> in <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">skillset.yaml</code> (must be higher than published)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Run the audit</strong> — it will detect the update and validate the version bump</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Submit</strong> — the PR will be titled "Update @author/name to vX.Y.Z"</li>
      </ol>
      <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto mt-4"><code># Edit skillset.yaml: version: "1.0.0" → "1.1.0"
npx skillsets audit   # Shows: Update: 1.0.0 → 1.1.0
npx skillsets submit  # Creates update PR</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-transparent p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink">Generated Structure</h2>
      <pre class="bg-white border border-border-ink p-4 rounded-none text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>your-skillset/
├── skillset.yaml          # Manifest (required)
├── README.md              # User instructions (required)
├── PROOF.md               # Production evidence (required)
├── AUDIT_REPORT.md        # Generated by audit commands
├── .claude/skills/        # Installed by init
│   └── skillset-audit/    # Qualitative review skill
└── content/               # Files to install
    ├── .claude/           # Claude Code settings
    └── CLAUDE.md          # Project instructions</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-transparent p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink">Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary font-serif">
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Production Proof:</strong> URL to a live product or repository showing real usage</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Complete Documentation:</strong> Clear README with installation and usage instructions</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Valid Schema:</strong> Must pass <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">skillset.yaml</code> validation</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Passing Audit:</strong> Generated by <code class="bg-white border border-border-ink px-2 py-1 rounded-none font-mono text-xs">npx skillsets audit</code></li>
        <li><strong class="text-text-ink">Verification-First:</strong> High friction ensures high quality</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-border-ink bg-stone-50 p-8 rounded-none mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-serif mb-4 text-text-ink border-b border-border-ink pb-2 inline-block">Manual Submission</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4 font-serif">
        Prefer to submit manually? You can fork the registry and open a PR directly.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/skillsets-cc/main"
        class="text-orange-500 font-mono font-bold hover:underline"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        View Registry →
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 text-center">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/skillsets-cc/main/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md"
        class="text-orange-500 font-mono font-bold hover:underline"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Read Full Contributing Guide →
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
